  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, 20–40 dm. Leaves: blade trullate to ovate or ovate-oblong, 3–7 cm, length/width = 1.5, lobes 4 per side, lobe apex acute, base broadly cuneate to truncate, adaxial surface glabrous, sometimes sparsely appressed-hairy along veins. Inflorescence branches glabrous. Flowers 15–22 mm diam.; stamens 10, anthers bright rose to dull purple, sometimes cream. 2n = 51.</description>
